Let $E$ be the foot of the altitude from $A$ to $\overline{BC}.$  Then $\triangle ADE$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle, so $AD = 2AE.$

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E;

A = (0,3);
B = (-1,0);
C = (4,0);
E = (A + reflect(B,C)*(A))/2;
D = extension(A,E,B,C);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--D);
draw(A--E);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, S);
label("$E$", E, NE);
[/asy]

By the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $ACE,$ $AE = \sqrt{AC^2 - CE^2} = \sqrt{3^2 - 1^2} = 2 \sqrt{2},$ so $AD = \boxed{4 \sqrt{2}}.$
